Former Eskom CEO Matshela Koko testifies at Zondo Commission * Editor's note: Livestream above courtesy DStv403. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom's former CEO Matshela Koko will give evidence at the state capture inquiry. Koko has been linked to several corrupt activities while at Eskom. It was revealed that his step-daughter received a tender worth R800-million from the power utility. WATCH: Koko's alleged reign of terror brings witness to tears Koko is said to have been personally involved in price negotiations and sometimes approved contract prices before
submission of proposals. Koko was one of four executives who were suspended by the power utility in 2015 pending an investigation. Currently, the Special Investigating Unit is trying to recoup some R3.8-billion lost to corruption from Koko and other past Eskom executives.